record.title: Land
record.detail: In 1789, Governor Phillip chose former convict James Ruse in an experiment to see how long it would take a man to support himself and his family. Ruse was granted cleared land, clothes and food for 15 months, and became successfully self-sufficient. In 1793, Ruse sold his farm to surgeon John Harris who built the substantial colonial Indian-style bungalow which still stands.
